RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 119 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WALK WITH ME went to the front, set the pace under pressure to her outside, vied along the rail on the turn, passed the five-sixteenths under coaxing, was asked for more outside the quarter-pole, responded well when put to the crop in upper stretch, was given final pop of the crop inside the furlong marker then held under a strong hand-ride to the finish. CALL HER BLUFF was coaxed along just off the pace, angled from the two path to the four path while placed under stronger encouragement on the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, remained on her inside lead until just before the furlong marker then swapped to the proper lead, gained into the final sixteenth and just missed. MANGIA brushed with a foe at the start, pressed the pace on the outside while in hand, was let out in the three path on the turn, came under a drive in upper stretch, battled with foes into the final furlong, dropped back into the final sixteenth and weakened. DOLCE VELOCE was rated just off the pace, moved from the inside to the two path early on the turn, drafted behind horses around that bend, was roused three wide into upper stretch, chased under a drive into the final furlong, moved out around the sixteenth-pole and tired. TONE OF SILENCE brushed with an opponent at the start, settled on the outside, dropped back leaving the backstretch, moved from the four path to the two path while falling well behind on the turn and faltered.

ENTRY.NAME: Call Her Bluff
ENTRY.OWNER: Rodriguez Rudy R Flying Zee Racing Stables LLC and LaBelle Tracey L

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPPORTUNITY SET was hustled from the gate, moved out early then advanced to the lead inside the seven-eighths pole, controlled the action in the two path on the turn, was roused outside the five-sixteenths pole, came under a right-handed crop outside the furlong marker, switched to a left-handed crop and was given one pop outside the sixteenth-pole then held under a solid hand-ride to the finish. UNION TAP bumped the hindquarters of I LOVE CARA while off slow then was slow into stride, settled at the rear, went two then three wide on the turn, came four wide into upper stretch and failed to threaten. LOUIE'S HEAT showed in front early, lost the lead inside the seven-eighths then stalked on the outside, dropped back in the four path under strong urging on the turn and retreated.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSIC DIVA came out in front then stumbled after the break, showed the way with a clear advantage, extended the lead while inside on the turn, responded well when put to the crop outside the furlong marker and proved much the best under strong urging. WISE CONVERSATION settled off the pace, moved from the rail to the two path on the turn, came five wide into upper stretch then moved further out and lacked the needed response. MOTHER MARY was ridden along towards the back, went five to six wide on the turn, moved in outside the furlong marker and failed to rally. SHE'S A LAKER climbed while off the pace near the five-eighths, went five then four wide on the turn and failed to respond. CARA'S GIRL dropped to the rear of the field on the backstretch, moved from the two path to the rail early on the turn, saved ground into the stretch and faltered.
